{"title":"Chris King DropSet 6 Headset Drops in for Downhill Bikes","link":"https://bikerumor.com/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-drops-in-for-downhill-bikes/","date":1707831000000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2500\" height=\"1667\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-2.jpg\" alt=\"chris king dropset 6 headset on a downhill mountain bike\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-2.jpg 2500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-2-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-2-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Chris King’s DropSet headset lineup now has an IS41/IS41 option for downhill bikes, fitting the straight 1-1/8″ steerer found on most double crown DH forks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This sixth iteration of their signature headset design has the same GripLock feature as the originals, and that’s the key benefit for rough-and-tumble riders like downhill racers.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2430\" height=\"1667\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-griplock-headset-description-diagram.jpg\" alt=\"chris king dropset 6 headset with exploded view diagram\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-griplock-headset-description-diagram.jpg 2430w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-griplock-headset-description-diagram-297x204.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-griplock-headset-description-diagram-800x549.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-griplock-headset-description-diagram-120x82.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-griplock-headset-description-diagram-768x527.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-griplock-headset-description-diagram-1536x1054.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-griplock-headset-description-diagram-2048x1405.jpg 2048w\" />\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t<figcaption>Closeup bike photos c. Keno Derleyn for Chris King.</figcaption>        <div>\n                \n                    \n                \n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"chris king dropset 6 headset with exploded view diagram\" /><figcaption>Closeup bike photos c. Keno Derleyn for Chris King.</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"chris king dropset 6 headset with exploded view diagram\" /><figcaption>Closeup bike photos c. Keno Derleyn for Chris King.</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n                <div></div>\n        </div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>What’s GripLock? Glad you asked.</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Chris King’s GripLock is a four-piece upper headset cap (E) that protects the headset bearing and prevents things from coming loose while riding. It works by stacking a wedge-shaped split ring (H) on top of the upper bearing ring (J). That ring nestles into the upper bearing (K), acting like a bearing race but for the bearing’s inner/top race, and then the wedge (H) literally wedges between the race and the fork’s steerer tube.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This sandwiched design distributes lateral loads from impacts (the bumps your hitting) away from the bearings, reducing stress on them. And if the upper race (J) tries to move upward, which would cause the headset to get loose, it constricts the split wedge (H), making it squeeze tighter onto the steerer, which prevents it from slipping upward, thus preventing the headset from becoming loose.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1582\" height=\"1055\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-1.jpg\" alt=\"chris king dropset 6 headset for DH downhill bikes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-1.jpg 1582w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-1-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-1-720x480.jpg 720w\" />\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t        <div>\n                \n                    \n                \n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"chris king dropset 6 headset for DH downhill bikes\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"chris king dropset 6 headset for DH downhill bikes\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div></div>\n        </div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, this makes it more difficult to remove a Chris King DropSet headset, but unless you’re swapping forks, there’s likely little need to have to remove it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new DropSet 6 headset is compatible with their included baseplate and all 45º integrated crown races. It’s also compatible with carbon and alloy steerer tubes. It’s available now in all of Chris King’s colors, plus two-tone black and gold. MSRP is $176 with steel bearings, or $296 with ceramic bearings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=28905&amp;pw=7185&amp;ctc=&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fchrisking.com%2Fcollections%2Fdropset%2Fproducts%2Fdropset%25E2%2584%25A2-6\">ChrisKing.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/chris-king-dropset-6-headset-drops-in-for-downhill-bikes/\">Chris King DropSet 6 Headset Drops in for Downhill Bikes</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"9af16c00a85ab351a690990c375bdf43195da1dcfe7c6eadedcefe3f23bf1582","category":"Cycling"}